The glucocorticoid receptor fluorescence polarization ligand binding (GRFP) assay is used to evaluate direct binding of testing compounds to full-length glucocorticoid (GR) protein. Reagents for this assay are purchased from Invitrogen in a test kit. A fluorescent labeled GR ligand is used as a fluorescent tracer and test compounds compete with the fluorescent tracer for GR binding. The glucocorticoid receptor fluorescence polarization ligand binding (GRFP) assay is used to evaluate direct binding of testing compounds to full-length glucocorticoid (GR) protein. Reagents for this assay are purchased from Invitrogen in a test kit. A fluorescent labeled GR ligand is used as a fluorescent tracer and test compounds compete with the fluorescent tracer for GR binding.
